Dark Days;;89;;94;;NC;;"Dark Days" is a feature length documentary about a community of homeless people living in a train tunnel beneath Manhattan. The film depicts a way of life which is unimaginable to most of those who walk the streets above. In the pitch blackness of the tunnel rats swarm through piles of garbage and high-speed trains out of Penn station tear through the darkness.;;Documentary;;Marc Singer;;2000;;Marc Singer;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dark_days